thread.title: Chinese Firm Pulls Out of Deal To Buy New Zealand Farms
thread.title_full: Chinese Firm Pulls Out of Deal To Buy New Zealand Farms - WSJ

author: Rebecca Howard
title: Chinese Firm Pulls Out of Deal To Buy New Zealand Farms
text:
WELLINGTON, New Zealand—Dakang New Zealand Farm Group, 55% owned by Shanghai Pengxin Group Co., said Monday it has pulled out of a deal to buy a group of farms on New Zealand’s North Island due to uncertainty from the government’s Overseas Investment Office.
Dakang entered into an agreement to buy the 3,300 hectares of land in January this year, which includes seven dairy and three support farms.
